 to every beneficiary family under the scheme to avail free and cashless treatments under the scheme. However, if anyone has lost his/her smart card, it can be re-issued by the district kiosk.", "002-normal": "The list of all the district kiosks is available at below link.  \n [List of District Kiosks](https://mhis.org.in/services)", "003-normal": "Modification of smart cards at these kiosks; whereby a name of a family member can be added to a smart card if the Beneficiary did not enroll themselves at the time of enrollment."}, "004-section": {"000-title": "Public Grievance and Helpline", "001-normal": "The complaints and grievances by the scheme beneficiaries can be made online at [this link](https://mhis.org.in/grievances) or contact at the phone numbers of respective district grievance redressal committee. The phone numbers are also available at the same link.", "002-normal": "The status of grievance can also be checked online on the same link on mhis.org.in."}, "005-section": {"000-title": "Highlights of Megha Health Insurance Scheme (MHIS)", "001-normal": "Below are some of the main highlights of MHIS", "002-listElement": "- In first and second phase, the government provided insurance coverage of Rs. 1,60,000 to each enrolled beneficiary family for an enrollment fee of Rs. 31 per annum.", "003-listElement": "- In the third phase, the government is providing insurance coverage of Rs. 2,80,000 for enrollment fee of Rs. 50 per annum for up to 5 members of a family on a floater basis.", "004-listElement": "- Senior citizens belonging to BPL and NREGA category would receive an additional insurance cover of Rs. 30,000.", "005-listElement": "- All pre-existing diseases are also covered under MHIS.", "006-listElement": "- The validity of an insurance policy is one year but it can be renewed by paying a nominal amount.", "007-listElement": "- The benefit of this scheme can only be availed in MHIS empaneled hospitals.", "008-listElement": "- In addition, the beneficiary 